p: In total, 13 compounds were identified in both types of hydrolates ( Table 4), and these compounds amounted to 84.1% in the H SD_SPE extracts and 85.1% in the H HD_SPE extracts. The main compounds in hydrolates were estragole and fenchone; both compounds formed almost 50% of the extracts. Estragole and fenchone are the major components of fennel EOs [ 35, 36, 37]. Furthermore, estragole was characterized as one of the key odorants in fennel EOs [ 38]. Another major constituent (often the most abundant compound) of fennel EOs, (E)-anethole, was not identified.
